modules.description: Provides functions to execute test suites with customizable command-line arguments and configuration options, and to define test cases that run asynchronously or synchronously. Works with test cases represented as tuples containing names, speed levels, and functions that take a context and return a deferred unit. Used to run tests with specific CLI flags, configure test behavior via command-line terms, and manage test execution flow and output.

Provides functions to define and execute unit tests, including a check function for asserting conditions and a run function for executing test callbacks. Works with testable values, unit-returning functions, and a query language for test selection. Used to validate code correctness with concise, colored feedback and targeted test execution.

Executes test suites with customizable command-line arguments and configurations, supporting both synchronous and asynchronous test cases. Tests are defined as tuples with names, speed levels, and functions that take a context and return a deferred unit. It allows running tests with specific CLI flags, managing execution flow, and handling asynchronous exceptions. Examples include running tests with timeout settings, filtering by speed, and capturing output during execution.
